All the councils in Scotland and Wales are being contested and some councils in England. In England, more than 4,000 council seats are being contested across 146 councils. In Scotland 1,200 seats are up in 32 council areas and in Wales there are 1,200 across 22 councils. The vote will be the first big test of public opinion since the Partygate scandal broke. FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES...